  ContentPartDonePartOutputText REQUIRES a `logprobs` field that the March-2025
  OpenAI cassette predates → pydantic ValidationError mid-stream (litellm's own
  parser, surfaced via the accumulator's on_error). This is litellm's data
  contract, not a weave bug — a real user on old data would hit it too.
- Final approach: authored clean, minimal, COHERENT SSE cassettes ("Write a
  one-sentence bedtime story about a unicorn." -> short story), validating every
  event through litellm's own `OpenAIResponsesAPIConfig.get_event_model_class(type)(**dict)`
  BEFORE writing. Non-streaming = plain JSON Response; streaming = validated SSE.

## Edge case -> base commit
A stream abandoned before response.completed leaves the accumulator on an
in_progress response with usage=None. model_dump() -> {model, usage: None, ...}.
weave_client's summary code did {**None} -> TypeError, leaving the call RUNNING
(corrupted trace). Fixed in the parent commit (andrew/tolerate-null-usage); see
its note. Consulted Codex (threadId 019ebd12...): Option A (fix core asymmetry)
as base PR, this feature stacked on top.

